  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get my songs converted to karaoke or instrumental?",
  "response": "Converting songs to karaoke or instrumental versions can be done in several ways. Here are some options you can explore:\n\n### 1. **Online Tools and Websites:**\n   - **Karaoke Creation Websites**: There are several websites that allow you to upload a song and remove the vocals. Some popular ones include:\n     - **Vocal Remover**: A free tool that can remove vocals from audio tracks.\n     - **PhonicMind**: AI-powered service that separates tracks and allows you to download instrumental versions.\n     - **melody.ml**: Another AI-based service to isolate vocals and instruments.\n\n### 2. **Digital Audio Workstations (DAWs):**\n   - Use software like **Audacity**, **FL Studio**, or **GarageBand** to manually edit your songs.\n   - In Audacity, you can use the \"Vocal Reduction and Isolation\" effect to minimize or remove vocals.\n\n### 3. **Karaoke Software:**\n   - Programs like **Karafun** or **Karaoke Builder Studio** allow you to create custom karaoke tracks with lyrics synced to music.\n\n### 4. **Professional Services:**\n   - Consider hiring a professional audio engineer or using a service like **Sing King** or **Karaoke Version**, which can produce high-quality instrumental tracks for you.\n\n### 5. **YouTube and Other Platforms:**\n   - Search for karaoke versions of your songs on platforms like YouTube, as many artists upload instrumental versions of popular songs.\n\n### 6. **VST Plugins:**\n   - If you're familiar with audio production, consider using plugins that isolate vocals or enhance certain frequencies, such as **iZotope RX** or **XTRAX STEMS**.\n\n### 7. **Create Your Own Karaoke:**\n   - If you want to take it a step further, use apps or software to record your own voice over an instrumental track, then you can create your own personalized karaoke.\n\n### 8. **Mobile Apps:**\n   - There are various apps available for both Android and iOS that can help you turn songs into karaoke. Look for apps like **Karaoke anywhere** or **Smule**.\n\n### Tips:\n- Make sure you have the necessary rights to use and modify the music if you plan to distribute it.\n- The quality of vocal removal can vary depending on the song's mix and complexity, so results might differ.\n\nChoose the method that best suits your needs based on your technical skills, the quality desired, and your budget.",
